  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>RepairQ offers the ability to integrate with Listen360\u00a0for engaging customers after the sale to encourage customer satisfaction and retention.\u00a0Enable the Listen360 integration to deliver closed tickets to your Listen 360 account on a nightly basis. Listen360 will then use this data to drive your customer engagement initiatives on their platform.</p><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: Before following this tutorial, please visit<strong>\u00a0</strong><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http://www.listen360.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>http://www.listen360.com/</strong></a> to request a demo and sign up for an account. You will need your FTP Username and FTP Password before integrating with RepairQ.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933443104/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"IntegrationSetup:Listen360-SettingupYourListen360IntegrationwithRepairQ\">Setting up Your Listen360 Integration with RepairQ</h2><p /><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Company Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933443104/Listen%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: Company Settings will affect all locations. If you would like to set up the integration for a single location, click <strong>Location Settings</strong>.</p><p /><p>2. On the Settings Overview page, click <strong>Integrations</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933443104/Listen%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. On the Integrations page, click <strong>Listen360</strong> from the Available Integrations section.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933443104/Listen%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. Enter your <strong>FTP User ID</strong> and <strong>FTP Password</strong>, then click the checkbox next to <strong>Enable Ticket Exports to Listen 360</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933443104/Listen%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>5. Click <strong>Save Listen 360 Settings</strong> to finalize the integration. RepairQ will deliver all closed ticket information to your Listen360 account on a nightly basis. You can contact your Listen360 representative for further instructions.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933443104/Listen%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: If you would like to turn off the integration, uncheck the box next to<strong> Enable Ticket Exports to Listen 360</strong>, and then click <strong>Save Listen 360 Settings</strong>.</p><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
      "representation": "export_view",
